.Dd May 28, 2026
.Dt XTC_MCTX 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_mctx_create ,
.Nm xtc_mctx_destroy ,
.Nm xtc_mctx_alloc ,
.Nm xtc_mctx_free ,
.Nm xtc_mctx_reset
.Nd hierarchical memory contexts with cleanup callbacks
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.In xtc_mctx.h
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_mctx_create "xtc_mctx_t *parent" "const char *name" "xtc_mctx_t **out"
.Ft void
.Fn xtc_mctx_destroy "xtc_mctx_t *ctx"
.Ft "void *"
.Fn xtc_mctx_alloc "xtc_mctx_t *ctx" "size_t size"
.Ft void
.Fn xtc_mctx_reset "xtc_mctx_t *ctx"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm xtc_mctx
is a hierarchical memory context, modeled on PostgreSQL's
.Vt MemoryContext .
Allocations belong to a context; destroying the context bulk-frees
everything in it
.Pq plus all child contexts recursively .
Useful for request-scoped memory: create a context per request,
allocate freely, destroy at the end without tracking individual
frees.
.Pp
Each context can register cleanup callbacks fired on destroy
.Pq before the bulk-free
to release non-memory resources.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
xtc_mctx_t *root, *req;
xtc_mctx_create(NULL, "root", &root);
xtc_mctx_create(root, "request-42", &req);

/* Allocate request-scoped objects. */
char *buf = xtc_mctx_alloc(req, 4096);
struct widget *w = xtc_mctx_alloc(req, sizeof *w);

/* Done; bulk-free everything in req. */
xtc_mctx_destroy(req);
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc_slab 3 ,
